      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mansfield_Center%2C_Connecticut"
    },
    {
      "id": 2,
      "text": "In 1702 the area was incorporated as a separate town and renamed for Major Moses Mansfield, an early settler.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        3
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Web source 2"
      ],
      "source": "https://www.britannica.com/place/Mansfield-Connecticut"
    },
    {
      "id": 3,
      "text": "The historic Mansfield Center Cemetery, featuring many 18th‑century gravestones, is listed on the National Register of Historic Places.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        6
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mansfield_Center%2C_Connecticut"
    },
    {
      "id": 4,
      "text": "The Barrows and Burnham Store, a general store built in 1886, stands as one of Mansfield Center’s historic buildings.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
        12
      ],
      "sourceLabels": [
        "Wikipedia"
      ],
      "source": "https://en.wikipedia.org/wiki/Mansfield_Center%2C_Connecticut"
    },
    {
      "id": 5,
      "text": "Mansfield Center’s census‑designated place also includes the village of Mansfield Hollow within the town.",
      "sourceSentenceIds": [
